Wash and dry all produce. Adjust rack to middle position and preheat oven to 450
degrees. Core, seed, and thinly slice @bell pepper{2}. Halve, peel, and thinly
slice @yellow onion{1}. Toss bell peppers and onion with @salt{}, @pepper{},
and a drizzle of @olive oil{1%drizzle} on a #baking sheet{}. Roast in oven until
tender, about ~{25%minutes}.

Toss @green beans{12%ounce} on another baking sheet with a drizzle of olive oil
and a pinch of salt and pepper. Roast in oven until tender and lightly crisped,
~{10-15%minutes}. Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @olive oil{} in a large pan over
high heat. Season @beef stir-fry{16%ounce} with salt, pepper, and
@Italian seasoning{1%tablespoon}.

Add half the beef to pan and cook, tossing occasionally, until browned,
~{2-4%minutes}. Remove from pan and set aside, then repeat with remaining beef.
Once bell peppers and onion are done roasting, toss with beef on same baking
sheet.

Split @demi-baguette{4} in half lengthwise, stopping before you cut all the way
through. Toast in oven until lightly golden, about ~{5%minutes}.

> TIP: Place the baguettes on the same sheet as the green beans, if there's room.

Wash out pan used for beef and return to stove over medium heat. Add
@butter{2%tablespoon} and let melt, then whisk in @flour{2%tablespoon}. Cook,
stirring frequently, until pasty and lightly toasted, about ~{1%minute}. Slowly
whisk in @milk{13.5%ounce}, adding a little at a time. Bring to a simmer and let
bubble, whisking, until thickened, about ~{1%minute}. Remove from heat and add
@cheddar cheese{1%cup}, stirring to melt.

Spread a little cheese sauce inside baguettes (save some for dipping), then fill
with bell peppers, onion, and beef. Sprinkle with @hot sauce{2%teaspoon}(to taste)
for the adults. Divide between plates and serve with green beans on the side.
Divide remaining cheese sauce between small #bowls{} for dipping.